title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Youth unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points.
Overall Youth unemployment rate has increased over the Year.

Youth unemployment rate is roughly constant from 1999 to 2000, slightly increasing from 2000 to 2001, slightly decreasing from 2001 to 2002, roughly constant from 2002 to 2005, slightly decreasing from 2005 to 2006, roughly constant from 2006 to 2010, slightly decreasing from 2010 to 2011, slightly increasing from 2011 to 2012, slightly decreasing from 2012 to 2013, rapidly increasing from 2013 to 2016, roughly constant from 2016 to 2017, slightly increasing from 2017 to 2018, and lastly roughly constant from 2018 to 2019.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2015 and 2016.
Max Youth unemployment rate about 37.24 was recorded at Year 2018
Min Youth unemployment rate about 28.43 was recorded at Year 2014
This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Youth unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points. The chart has 6 significant trends.
The longest trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 2005 to 2010.
Differently, the next significant trend is moderately decreasing which exists from 2016 to 2019.
But, the next significant trend is extremely decreasing which exists from 2013 to 2016.
On the contrary, the next significant trend is moderately increasing which exists from 2010 to 2013.
In a similar manner, the next significant trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 2002 to 2005.
But, the next significant trend is moderately increasing which exists from 1999 to 2002.
